  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The development shall be carried out in accordance with the reports, specifications and drawings detailed: Site location plan; PY4056/002 (Existing Elevations); PY4056/005 (Elevations); PY4623-015-001 (Site Plan); Cover letter dated 01/07/2024 by New World Payphones; New Communications Kiosk Overview and Specification. \r\nReason: To ensure a satisfactory standard of development and to allow the local planning authority to review any potential changes to the scheme. \r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The maximum steady brightness of the advertisement hereby permitted is not to exceed 300 candelas per sqm. \r\nReason: To ensure the sign does not have an adverse effect on the amenity of the area in accordance with policy LP9 of the Local Plan and to comply with paragraph 141 of the National Planning Policy Framework.\r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - The advertisements must be static and contain no moving features, flashing, animation, intermittent light source or exposed cold cathode tubing. Sequential advertisements displayed via the unit permitted by this consent shall not change more than once every 10 seconds. The interval between successive displays shall take place over a period no greater than one second; the complete screen shall change with no visual effects (including fading, swiping or other animated transition methods) between displays and the display will include a mechanism to freeze the image in the event of a malfunction. \r\nReason: In the interest of highway safety and of the visual amenities of the locality in accordance with policy LP9 of the Local Plan and to comply with the National Planning Policy Framework.\r\n",
    "Condition : 4 - No music or sound shall be emitted from the advertisements. \r\nReason: In the interest of the aural amenities of the locality in accordance with policies LP2 and LP9 of the Local Plan.\r\n"
  ],
